title: Loans and Discounts, National Banks, Central Reserve Cities for United States
notes:
Monthly Coverage Varies From Year To Year. All Years Have Scattered Five Month Coverage, Except For 1882 Which Has Only Coverage For October And December, And 1914 Which Has Coverage For Six Months. Overdrafts Were Added By NBER Whenever Itemized Separately. Data Include Chicago, New York, And St. Louis. Source: Annual Reports Of The Comptroller Of The Currency.

This NBER data series m14019 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
